│ 1907 /// A pure virtual base class for all recipes modeling  │
│ header phis, including                                       │
│ 1908 /// phis for first order recurrences, pointer           │
│ inductions and reductions. The                               │
│ 1909 /// start value is the first operand of the recipe and  │
│ the incoming value from                                      │
│ 1910 /// the backedge is the second operand.                 │
│ 1911 ///                                                     │
│ 1912 /// Inductions are modeled using the following          │
│ sub-classes:                                                 │
│ 1913 ///  * VPCanonicalIVPHIRecipe: Canonical scalar         │
│ induction of the vector loop,                                │
│ 1914 ///    starting at a specified value (zero for the main │
│ vector loop, the resume                                      │
│ 1915 ///    value for the epilogue vector loop) and stepping │
│ by 1. The induction                                          │
│ 1916 ///    controls exiting of the vector loop by comparing │
│ against the vector trip                                      │
│ 1917 ///    count. Produces a single scalar PHI for the      │
│ induction value per                                          │
│ 1918 ///    iteration.                                       │
│ 1919 ///  * VPWidenIntOrFpInductionRecipe: Generates vector  │
│ values for integer and                                       │
│ 1920 ///    floating point inductions with arbitrary start   │
│ and step values. Produces                                    │
│ 1921 ///    a vector PHI per-part.                           │
│ 1922 ///  * VPDerivedIVRecipe: Converts the canonical IV     │
│ value to the corresponding                                   │
│ 1923 ///    value of an IV with different start and step     │
│ values. Produces a single                                    │
│ 1924 ///    scalar value per iteration                       │
│ 1925 ///  * VPScalarIVStepsRecipe: Generates scalar values   │
│ per-lane based on a                                          │
│ 1926 ///    canonical or derived induction.                  │
│ 1927 ///  * VPWidenPointerInductionRecipe: Generate vector   │
